<head><title>Internet Pinball Machine Database: Viza 'War'</title>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="imagetoolbar" CONTENT="no">
<meta name="keywords" content="IPD IPDB Internet Pinball Machine Database Game Viza War Head-to-Head Play Flippers (8), Pop bumpers (2), Slingshots (2), Kick-out holes (2). Electronic LED scoring.

Sound: 3 chimes.

This is a head-to-head game where two players at opposite ends of the playfield compete in simultaneous play. Each player has flipper buttons which control only those flippers facing the opponent. Game can also be played as a single player. Ball enters play from outhole by pressing red button on front of cabinet next to coin slots. Ball through center 'fli<ignore>pper kill area' rollover lane renders opponent's flippers inoperative for a preset period of time (operator adjustable).  ">
<meta name="Description" content="Pictures, documents, manufacturing data, ratings, comments, features, and history for Viza 'War' pinball machine.">
